    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">464.11 W 89/12</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Western European Affairs,
                        Department of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Castle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Grew</hi>: Mr. Pelenyi, Hungarian Chargé, came to see
                    me this morning to say that he had received authorization from his Government
                    for the signing of the agreement for a mixed claims commission. He said,
                    however, that this authorization to sign was made out in the name of the
                    Minister and Count Szechenyi will not be back in this country before the end of
                    October. He said, therefore, that instead of sending the papers to us he was at
                    the moment merely informing us that the authorization had arrived so that, if
                    the Department so desired, the papers could be ready when the Minister reaches
                    Washington.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. E. C[<hi rend="smallcaps">astle</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
